The paper proposes a novel boundary-aware network for image-based salient object detection, which involves the use of deep learning techniques and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of complex interior perception stream and transition compensation stream, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the second likely category. The paper also involves the use of extensive experiments and comparisons with state-of-the-art methods, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely category. The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper involves the use of boundary localization and feature enhancement techniques, which suggests the involvement of information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) the fifth likely category.
